Sit down because this is going to be one long post. <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> But</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->,you will not find anything like it on this forum. Definately a must read.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Why we need a Support Team</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Most raiders don't see what goes on behind the scenes. The pathway to a Dragon's Lair is not easy. It takes knowledge and experienced raiders to clear and pull the lair.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Vox</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
There are 2 Ice Giants that spawn every 30 minutes.There are 9 Ice Giants, 2 spiders, and 2 icy terrors that are on a 3 hour spawn timer.There are pits leading up to and surrounding her lair. Pits with bears, wolves, spiders, and icy terrors, just waiting for a snack.<br>
And we've just gotten to the lair. Inside you find 4 Ice Giants, 1 Fire Giant (Naggy's priest), 2 icy terrors, and Lady Vox. All except Vox are also on a 3 hour spawn timer. If a level 52 or under goes into Vox's lair.. chance are they will die. If a level 53 or higher goes into Vox's lair... they may die from Ice Giants etc..but Vox cannot touch them. If any mob in the lair sees them, she banishes them from the Zone. Yes they end up in Everfrost just outside the Permafrost zone. So besides pulling the lair, timing is the biggest factor. If the lair is pulled too early, it could mean all those baddies popping on top of the buffline, or during Corpse Retrieval. And sometime Corpse Retrieval is done with Vox still alive. Ice Giants repopping is NOT a pretty sight.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Nagafen</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
From the zone in to Sol B, raiders may have to pass kobolds, sonic bats, lava duct crawlers, beetles, and stone spiders. Depending on if these are camped or not, the actually raiders will usually have to clear as they go due to spawn rates. Once we reach the Fire Giant areas (they are tougher than Ice Giants) there are 15 Fire Giants, including King Tranix and Warlord Skarlon. Inside the Lair is 3 Fire Giants and Lord Nagafen. One of the Fire Giants is right behind Naggy (kissing up Im sure). Same rules here for Dragon Aggro. Under level 53 is slaughtered, over level 53 is banished to outside the zone. All Fire Giants are on a 7-8 hour spawn timer. So killing them during a raid, we usually don't worry about Fire Giant repops. BUT there have been times when we have gone in and most of the Fire Giants are dead (even though there is a rule that the guilds on our server have promised to follow about NOT killing FG's if Nagafen is up. More people need to be educated about it). Who killed them? When did they kill them? Will they respawn during raiding, buffing, etc? Nice to have a support team to deal with any unexpected repops.<br>
<br>
Support team does ALOT more than sit on the wrong ramps to Vox's lair. They risk as much, if not more, than those actually killing the dragon. They clear the path, keep it clear, time repops, and do Corpse Retrieval. After a total wipeout, a good support team can make the difference between a 5 hour Corpse Retrieval and a 1 hour Corpse Retrieval.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Buffline</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Most of our buffline consists of actual raiders. Occasionally we are graced with higher levels and thier buffs, summoned items, and mana songs. Many do not think buffs are too important. Dragons dispell. Why it is important to get your buffs in the proper order. Do you want your HP buff dispelled first? I think not. Getting the proper buffs and in the correct order are crucial to the outcome of a raid.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Trust. Respect. Attitude</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Trust</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
When you go on a raid, you put your trust in that raid leader. If they say &quot;Charge!&quot; you do even if you don't agree or understand why. If you don't have that trust, then don't go on the raid. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Respect</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Respect all those around you. Two types of repsect. One is given freely and the other is earned. <br>
Respect given freely is giving someone the benefit of the doubt, being aware of others feelings, treating that person as a human being even if you don't agree completely with what they are saying or doing.<br>
Respect earned is entirely between the two people involved. It is earned thru words and actions, or lack thereof. It is earned thru upholding values.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Attitude</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Your attitude does not just affect you. It affects all you come in contact with. Attitude can be just your being in general or it can be focused at a cetain item, situation, or person. <br>
<br>
These three attributes have always been a concern to me, in and out of the game, in all my dealings.<br>
<br>
Different people, different opinions, different perspectives, different goals. I would like to think that all who come on KCoG raids have the same goal. But I am fully aware that is not the case. There is nothing wrong with having different priorities and goals. But to accomplish what you desire from the game you need to be with those who have the same goals, attitudes, and focus, as your own. <br>
If you are not here to have fun, meet your fellow Karanians, and experience the thrill of working together to take down a dragon, then go somewhere else.<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------<br>
All that being said, I would like to address the comments and concerns of this post.<br>
I do believe that people took advantage of a substitute raid leader last night. I was there mainly as an observer and organizing the buffline. I observed alot of comments and behavior I did not like.<br>
Last night is the most we have ever had show up for support team. We had alot of new faces and also those who have continued to support KGoC events over and over.<br>
<br>
The <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> attitude</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of the support team should be first and foremost to &quot;support&quot; the raiders, not for loot. But I also feel that they sacrifice enough to be given an option to lotto on dragon loot. I usually KNOW my support team and they have come to more than one raid with me. I am also willing to give those I don't know a fair chance. So at this point it comes to a matter of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> trust</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. I trust my support team to roll on items that they <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> need</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and not just something they will give away, sell, or can get from another source. This shows <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> respect</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for your fellow players. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Support team will still be able to lotto for items.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
As far as support team bringing alts and rolling, it has always had to be approved by the raid leader. For an example, one of our support/ buff team had a cleric for the raiding and a druid for the buffing. Obviously clerics are very important to a raid. But last night we were in need of a druid to cast Circle of Summer. So she toggled between two toons. Usually in cases as this, the player may chose to roll for either the cleric OR the druid, but not both. And the toon they are rolling for HAS to be involved in the raid in some way.. either as support or raider. This actually occurs quite often but ALWAYS has to be approved by the raid leader ahead of time.<br>
<br>
I always try to be unbiased and fair, and not showing any favoritism. I listen to people's concerns and post when necessary. Periodically I do review the loot rules, strategys, buff line up, etc... things to improve the overall experience yet keeping in mind with the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> true spirit</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of the KCoG. <br>
